A truck driver and his passenger are recovering in hospital after being involved in a collision with a train near Addo on Tuesday afternoon. Police spokesperson Sergeant Majola Nkohli said the incident took place at about 3pm at a railway crossing in Valencia. He said details surrounding the incident were sparse. “It is alleged the truck collided with a train at a railway crossing. “Police are investigating a case of reckless and negligent driving. “The truck driver and his passenger sustained injuries, and were rushed to the nearest hospital,” Nkohli said. HeraldLIVE